\cos^2 (\theta x) - 1 = 0
\pi
\cos^2n=\frac12+\frac{\cos2n}2
n=\theta x
\frac12\cos2\theta x-\frac12=0
\cos2\theta x=1
2\theta x=2k\pi
-\sin^2\theta x=0
(\cos\theta x-1)(\cos\theta x+1)=0
\cos 2x=\cos^2x-\sin^2x=2\cos^2x-1
\cos^2(x\theta)-1=\frac{\cos (2x\theta)-1}{2}
\cos^2(x\theta)-1=0\iff \cos(2x\theta)=1\iff 2x\theta=2k\pi\,,\,k\in\Bbb Z\ldots
